io.werval.api

Interface Application

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ApplicationSPI 

    public interface Application
    Application.

    An Application instance can run in different Modes, default Mode is Mode.TEST. For your code to be Mode.DEV friendly, don't hold references to instances returned by an Application instance.

        void activate()
       throws ActivationException
        Activate the Application.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if the Application is already active.
        ActivationException - if something goes wrong.

      • passivate

        void passivate()
        Passivate the Application.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if the Application was not active.

      • isActive

        boolean isActive()
        Application activation state.
        Returns:

      • plugin

        <T> T plugin(Class<T> pluginApiType)
        Lookup a Plugin's API.

        Don't hold references to the Plugins API instances in order to make your code Mode.DEV friendly.

        Type Parameters:
        T - Parameterized Plugin API type
        Parameters:
        pluginApiType - Plugin type
        Returns:
        The first Plugin API found that match given type (Type equals first, then assignable).
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if no Plugin is found for the given API type
        IllegalStateException - if the Application is not active

      • plugins

        <T> Iterable<T> plugins(Class<T> pluginApiType)
        Lookup possibly several Plugin's API.

        Don't hold references to the Plugins API instances in order to make your code Mode.DEV friendly.

        Type Parameters:
        T - Parameterized Plugin API type
        Parameters:
        pluginApiType - Plugin type
        Returns:
        All Plugin APIs found that match the he given type (Type equals first, then assignables), or none if no Plugin is found for the given API type.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if the Application is not active
